188.3	Local_food	Local food	Local food or the local food movement is a "collaborative effort to build more locally based, self-reliant food economies - one in which sustainable food production, processing, distribution, and consumption is integrated to enhance the economic, environmental and social health of a particular place." It is part of the concept of local purchasing and local economies; a preference to buy locally produced goods and services rather than those produced by corporatized institutions.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/Marylebone_Farmers_Market_2005.jpg/220px-Marylebone_Farmers_Market_2005.jpg
